dataLineage.statement:
Layer was created by ITOS by converting the Sudan Admin2 polygon layer to lines. The lines were created after all processing on the admin layer had been completed by ITOS. Lines have been added for the north boundary of "Bir Tawil" and the south boundary of the "Halayib triangle". These boundaries are only present in the lines layer.
An 'AdminLevel' field is used to attribute the lines. The values used for this field are: (0,1,2,3,4,5,99). 99 represents coastline. 0 is international border, 1 is Admin1 border, 2 is Admin2 border, etc. Each line is attributed with the highest admin level that it can participate in.
